      <div id="centre2" class="centre">
       <img title="RYA Training" src="images/training.jpg" />
       <h1>
        RYA Training
       </h1>
       <div class="clear">
       </div>
       <div style="float:right; margin-top:-20px; margin-left:15px; width:280px;">
        <img title="RYA Training Centre" src="images/training_centre.jpg" style="padding:0px 10px 10px 40px;" />
        <p style="padding-left:40px;">
         <strong>
          <u>
           RYA PW Proficiency Course
          </u>
         </strong>
         <br />
         Course duration - 1 day, 9.30 - 5.30 approx
         <br />
         Minimum age - 18 yrs (Tor Bay Harbour bye law)
         <br />
         Previous experience - None required
        </p>
        <ul>
         <strong>
          <u>
           Course content
          </u>
         </strong>
         <li>
          Personal equipment, Safety Kit
         </li>
         <li>
          Launching &amp; Recovery, trailer safety
         </li>
         <li>
          Correct use of kill cord
         </li>
         <li>
          Boarding and re-boarding in deep water
         </li>
         <li>
          Steering, Control &amp; Trim
         </li>
         <li>
          Low &amp; high speed handling
         </li>
         <li>
          Man overboard recovery
         </li>
         <li>
          Coming alongside / Marina handling
         </li>
         <li>
          Towing &amp; Emergency situations
         </li>
         <li>
          Basic navigation &amp; passage planning
         </li>
         <li>
          Collision Regs, Weather &amp; Tides
         </li>
         <li>
          Aftercare &amp; Maintenance
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="padding-left:40px;">
         <strong>
          <u>
           Course fees
          </u>
         </strong>
         <br />
         Weekday group courses (excluding WaveRunner hire) - £150.00 per person, minimum 2 persons per course
         <br />
         <br />
         Weekend &amp; bank holiday group courses  (excluding WaveRunner hire) - £175.00 per person, minimum 2 persons per course
         <br />
         <br />
         Private one to one course - £279.00 anytime
        </p>
        <ul>
         <strong>
          <u>
           Whats included in the cost?
          </u>
         </strong>
         <li>
          RYA Personal Watercraft Handbook
         </li>
         <li>
          RYA certificate upon successful completion
         </li>
         <li>
          Use of our wetsuits, buoyancy aids &amp; footwear
         </li>
        </ul>
       </div>
       <p>
        <strong style="font-size:14px;">
         Gliddon Marine is an authorised Yamaha WaveRunner dealer and RYA Training Centre. We offer the RYA Personal Watercraft Proficiency Course to clients from our shore base at Churston Ferrers and at Brixham Marina plus an introduction to the sport through our Yamaha WaveRunner Taster and Safari sessions.
        </strong>
       </p>
       <p>
        Participants can undertake the PW Proficiency course as part of a group or on a private 1-to-1 basis with an instructor. Whether you would like to get more out of your own PW or are keen to learn the ropes before buying one, or want a great day out with friends or family with the added bonus of everyone learning how to safely use a Personal Watercraft, this course covers it all. No previous experience is necessary and the course will give students the confidence and knowledge to safely operate a personal watercraft.
       </p>
       <p>
        The RYA PW Proficiency Certificate is recognised by most UK insurers, many of whom offer a discount to holders. Many local harbour authorities, Tor Bay included, offer launching discounts to holders and some UK harbour authorities will not permit you to launch without one. You must have the certificate if you plan to use your PW abroad.
       </p>
       <p>
        The courses are run by Simon Gliddon, Centre Principal, and Neil Rickard, Chief Instructor, in a fun and enjoyable manner at a pace to suit everyone in the beautiful and sheltered waters of Tor Bay. If you don't yet have your own ski we can rent you one of our 2013 Yamaha VX Cruiser's for the course. Maybe you'd like to get involved in the sport but have never even sat on a PW? No problem - this course is for you too!
       </p>
       <p>
        <strong>
         <u>
          WaveRunner hire for training courses
         </u>
        </strong>
        <br />
        2013 Yamaha VX Cruiser - £84 per PWC (includes fuel and insurance)
        <br />
        We run courses throughout the year to suit. Please contact us on 01803 842245 (option 2) with your requirements or for an informal chat, or drop us a mail to
        <a href="mailto:info@gliddonmarine.co.uk">
         info@gliddonmarine.co.uk
        </a>
        . The course numbers are limited to a maximum of 6 students using 3 PW's, max 2 persons per PW. You will maximise your benefit and enjoyment of the course riding solo. If you are bringing your own ski it must be registered with Tor Bay Harbour Authority (the cost is a £15.00 one-off fee) and you must be insured. Please note, we do NOT hire our WaveRunners for any other purpose than for instruction or taster sessions nor are we permitted to do so. All prices include vat where applicable.
       </p>
      </div>
